---
import TextRegistryRespec from "@/components/respec/TextRegistryRespec.astro";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset='utf-8'>
    <title>WCAG 3 Text Metrics Registry</title>
    <TextRegistryRespec />
    <script is:inline src="https://www.w3.org/Tools/respec/respec-w3c" class="remove"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <section id='abstract'>
        <p>This registry is intended to provide a framework for [[wcag-3.0]] to include text metrics from a wide range of scripts and languages. Including specific text metrics in the main document is prohibitive in terms of how to present multiple languages. Separating the specific metrics for different scripts from the main document allows for scripts to be added independantly to the recommendation. Ultimately this supports quicker adoption as more is learned about the needs of readers of different scripts and languages.</p> 
        <p>The registy is non-normative.</p>
    </section>

    <section id='sotd'>
        <p>To comment, <a href="https://github.com/w3c/wcag3/issues/new">file an issue in the W3C wcag3 GitHub repository</a>. The Working Group requests that public comments be filed as new issues, one issue per discrete comment. It is free to create a GitHub account to file issues. If filing issues in GitHub is not feasible, email <a href="mailto:public-agwg-comments@w3.org?subject=WCAG%203.0%20public%20comment">public-agwg-comments@w3.org</a> (<a href="https://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/public-agwg-comments/">comment archive</a>). In-progress updates to the registry can be viewed in the <a href="https://w3c.github.io/wcag3/text-registry/">public editors’ draft</a>.</p>
    </section>

